  <h3 style="text-align:center">Objective</h3>

  <p style="margin-left:20%;margin-right:20%">In 2014, I was approached by the Anglo Italian home automation company Domotz to come up with designs for their home automation mobile application. The challenge here was to complete the design in 20 hours.</p><br />

  <h3 style="text-align:center">My Role</h3>

  <p style="margin-left:20%;margin-right:20%">The idea is to represent the master panel for 50 devices present in a house. The master panel should allow access to complete details of each device and controls to them. This must be achieved in one page on a tablet device, a page which can be scrollable/swipeable.</p><br />

  <h3 style="text-align:center">Outcome</h3>

  <p style="margin-left:20%;margin-right:20%">The layout and system produced displays all the 50 devices in one page (scroll up or down) and provides basic direct usable details readily on the initial screen. When extended detail is required, the device is selected and the screen expands to display the detailed information i.e. the 50x”12”s 12 extra parameter section. Once the necessary tasks are performed and the view is then collapsed and the user can move to another device by scrolling up or down.I came up with three different designs, each transitioning to the next, leading to a final design which formed the basis of domotz’s current mobile User Interface and Experience.

  </p><br />

